args: The grimoire section of the library here is\nSO lame. I read everything in a day!
There has to be a decent book somewhe...\nUgh. Here comes the pompous buffoon.
Ha HA! Another splendid day of peace and\nobeisance throughout my castle.
The help are smiling their charming,\ncommoner smiles, and all is as it sho...\nUgh, it's that swaggering ninny.
Hey! Make room for a genius here!
It is YOU who will make way, serf!\nA king does not step aside for the help.\nIt simply is not done.
There's only one ruler in this castle,\nbub, and he ain't you.
Now take your puffed-up airs and move\n'em two feet to the left!
If you're going to squabble, do it outside.
This is hardly a squabble. I'm simply\neducating this woman about her proper\nsocial station.
Oh yeah? So what's the social station for\n＂used to be a king before his own people\nthrew him out＂?

How DARE you?! I was willing to let you
off with a stern warning given your obvious
lack of proper boarding-school education,
but this insult will not stand!

I know you have named yourself as some
manner of ＂genius,＂ but no amount of
bookish learning can change your birth.
You, madam, shall always be common!
You two are a perfect match.
If your egos were any larger, they wouldn't\nfit inside your bodies.
Shall we settle the pecking order for good?\nWould that put an end to this idiocy?
A brilliant idea! ...Especially considering\nit comes from one of my lesser vassals.
You're on! One spell, and I'll have you\nfried to a crisp!
No violence. We keep this peaceful.
I will choose the contest, and I alone\nwill judge the victor. Is that acceptable?
Fine! There isn't a competition in the world\nthis stuffed shirt could beat me at.
I accept your terms as well, good woman,\nfor a king fears no challenge!
Then we're agreed. Now, let's take this to\na more fitting venue.
Now then. The event I've selected is...
Laundry. Whoever gets their pile cleaner\nfaster wins.
Hey! I'm talkin' here! LAUNDRY?!\nIs this some kind of joke?
The contest has already begun.\nOr do you forfeit?
Ha HA! How terribly lowborn of you.\nIt seems victory is already mine.
Some genius, if a little bit of washing is\nenough to send you packing.
Okay, I've heard enough from you two!
I'm a genius at everything—stupid laundry\nincluded. Watch and be amazed!
Washtub water, churn and spin.\nHelp this genius girl to win!
Impressive. The force of the whirlpool is\nbreaking up even the stubborn pottage\nstains, leaving behind a sparkling white.
Now THAT'S how you do laundry.\nLet's see you try, Lord Tightbritches.
I'll bet you've never washed your own\nclothes once in your life, you spoiled—
Ah, but there you would be wrong.\nBehold the king of washing!
That fluid motion... That technique...\nHow the heck are you GOOD at this?!
Ha HA! Do you see now, churl?\nI told you a king fears no challenge!
I have been living in exile ever since my\nvassals staged their coup.
In my months of wandering, I've learned\nhow to manage rather well on my own.
How did you make THAT sound pompous?!
That is my kingly aura you're finally\ndetecting! ...Rather slow on the uptake,\naren't you?
Rgh... W-well, I was still faster!
A magnificent showing from both of you.\nI fear it's too close to call.
We'll simply have to hold another contest\nand break the tie.
I've other matters of state to attend to!\n...But I suppose this must come first.
Dusting. The armory is a pigsty.
Oh, this is gonna be a piece of cake...\nWinds, sweep all these weapons neat.\nHand this dolt a swift defeat!
Er, Ezelith?! Using wind magic will only\nkick up all the...
...dust? My goodness. The whirlwind\ntrapped it all and blew it out the window.
Leaving the armory spotless, I might add.\nThere's nothing left to clean here!
If that isn't a clear victory, I don't know\nwhat is.
Ha HA! Oh, you poor, naive thing.
The armory has been cleaned to perfection\nwithout me so much as lifting a finger.
THIS is how a king dusts—by having his\nvassals and lackeys do it for him!
Could your logic BE any more tortured?!\nJudge, back me up here!
You have a point about the torture...
But you said yourself that it was logic.\nI'm afraid we have another tie.
Okay, that is just STUP... Rrrrgh!\nNever mind. You'll just disqualify me\nif I complain.
Next is a cooking showdown.\nLet's move to the kitchen and—
Cooking, is it? An easy victory!
In your dreams! I'm going to crush you\nlike an egg filled with grapes filled with\nsomething else really crushable!
No running in the castle, you two! *sigh*\nThey really are a perfect match...
I wonder if they'll catch on before my\nchores are done?
Yeah, we need you in the kitchen to judge!
All right, all right, I'm coming.\nIt's a cooking contest, not a race.
Neither king nor genius sits at the\ntop of the castle pecking order—
